      "writtenOn": "2016-04-18T18:39:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree on the .c --\u003e .cpp conversion.  I don\u0027t know how well our tools handle such renames when it comes time to merge with qemu -- but if the answer is \"pretty well\", then I think that we ought to be fairly aggressive on such conversions.  If we\u0027re not, then there might be n such mods to a file over time, where none of them individually justify the conversion, but where the sum of them certainly do.\n\nWRT whether it\u0027s actually simpler: I think it is objectively simpler to use ScopedCPtr.  A declaration of that here, replacing \"owns_tz\", a \"reset\" of that where you set owns_tz to true, and you get to eliminate the \"if (owns_tz) free(...)\".  Better, I don\u0027t have to reason about whether that code is reached -- especially given that there\u0027s a label above that\u0027s the target of a goto, and a \"return\".",
